<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-05-22T07:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-05-22T07:00:00-05:00" n="109" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d109">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">340.1115A/663: Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Ireland</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Gray</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Dublin</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-05-22T13:00:00+01:00">May
                                        22, 1940—1 p.m.</date>
                                    <lb/> [Received May 22—8:32 a.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>20. Consul’s preliminary estimate indicates probably less than 600
                                Americans in Ireland desirous to return. No new arrivals.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Gray</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>